This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a boosting framework for Factorization Machines, which is a popular machine learning model for recommendation systems. It may also belong to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) as recommendation systems are often used in information retrieval applications. Additionally, it may belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as machine learning is a key component of AI. The paper also involves experiments on real-world datasets, which suggests it may belong to the sub-categories of data science (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
